## How this file evolves

- A phase ships → flip its row in [`progression.md`](./progression.md). Don't edit this file unless scope changed.
- A phase's scope changes mid-flight → log a row in [`decisions.md`](./decisions.md), update the In/Out here, note the change in [`progression.md`](./progression.md)'s log.
- A new phase is needed in the middle → renumber everything after; both humans and agents look for "Phase N", numbering matters.
- A phase is too big to ship in one go → split it. Two smaller phases beat one long phase of "almost there."
